From fb0e292f6e89098e34cd9dc0d5a799693ebbe8ac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 20:32:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Sync examples with current records_list_types systematic

Bring the example Timeline and Catalog Fluid templates fully in line
with the current records_list_types template systematic so they keep
working as the main extension evolves:

- shared TableHeading partial for the table heading (single-table mode
  + multi-record-selection panel)
- TYPO3 core f:sanitize.html(build: 'records-list-types-backend-fragments')
  for TYPO3-generated backend fragments (action buttons, multi-record-
  selection actions)
- TYPO3 14 native <typo3-backend-contextual-record-edit-trigger> for
  every record edit link (titles, image links, edit buttons)
- permission-aware action rendering using the precomputed
  record.permissions.* flags (canEdit, canToggleVisibility, canDelete,
  canShowInfo, canHistory, canCopy)
- 'More actions' popover button (popovertarget + popover) mirroring the
  built-in Card / TeaserCard / CompactRow partials
- shared Pagination partial for single-table pagination
- multi-record-selection wiring (data-multi-record-selection-* attributes
  + checkbox name="CBC[table|uid]") gated on table.multiSelectEnabled

Add translatable XLIFF labels for every example view type (Timeline,
Catalog, Address Book, Event List, Gallery, Dashboard) plus the
template strings (No image, Hidden, Edit, Show, Hide, Delete, More
actions, Info, History, Copy, Cut), in English and German, and switch
the TSconfig labels and descriptions to LLL: references that resolve
through the standard XLIFF override mechanism. The image preview hint
keeps reusing the existing image.previewOnly translation from the main
records_list_types extension.

Drop the dead partialRootPath references from setup.tsconfig (no
custom partials shipped here; the built-in records_list_types partial
paths are already fallback paths).

Refresh README accordingly.
